'''Will Dobson''' (born 7 September 2007).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/dobson-will/IgtWVtI0/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en-AU}}</ref> is an Australian professional [[soccer]] player who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].

== Youth Career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===
Will Dobson joined the Newcastle Jets Academy in 2022 after a two year spell away with [[Weston Bears FC]], where he played in their U16s<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson - Player Statistics |url=https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?pID=207383317 |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=GameDay |language=en}}</ref> as a 14 year old.

He made his debut for the [[Newcastle Jets FC Youth|Jets Youth]] team in 2023, coming off the bench against [[Hurstville ZFC]] as a 15 year old<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match Centre - Dribl Match Centre |url=https://competitions.footballnsw.com.au/matchcentre/?m=3NPo2R5Z0m |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=competitions.footballnsw.com.au}}</ref>. He scored his first goal for the Youth team in the 2024 [[Football NSW League]] Two season against [[South Coast Flame FC]], going on to finish that campaign with 7 goals in 26 games as the Jets Youth went unbeaten and earned promotion into FNSW League One<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-05 |title=Champion youth team shows Newcastle Jets on right flight path |url=https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/8719319/jets-youth-secure-nsw-npl1-spot-with-record-breaking-season/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.newcastleherald.com.au |language=en-au}}</ref>.

== Club career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===

==== Debut Season (2024-25) ====
Ahead of the [[2024–25 A-League Men|2024–25 A-League]] season, Dobson was awarded a two-year scholarship deal<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-08-16 |title=Will Dobson signs scholarship deal |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/will-dobson-signs-scholarship-deal/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref> by Head Coach [[Robert Stanton (soccer)|Robert Stanton]]. He made his debut off of the bench in round one against Melbourne City.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-20 |title=Academy Product Will Dobson makes Professional Debut |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/academy-product-will-dobson-makes-professional-debut/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref>. Dobson made his first start later on that season against Perth Glory.

'''Will Dobson''' (born 7 September 2007).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/dobson-will/IgtWVtI0/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en-AU}}</ref> is an Australian professional [[soccer]] player who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].

== Youth Career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===
Will Dobson joined the Newcastle Jets Academy in 2022 after a two year spell away with [[Weston Bears FC]], where he played in their U16s<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson - Player Statistics |url=https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?pID=207383317 |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=GameDay |language=en}}</ref> as a 14 year old.

He made his debut for the [[Newcastle Jets FC Youth|Jets Youth]] team in 2023, coming off the bench against [[Hurstville ZFC]] as a 15 year old<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match Centre - Dribl Match Centre |url=https://competitions.footballnsw.com.au/matchcentre/?m=3NPo2R5Z0m |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=competitions.footballnsw.com.au}}</ref>. He scored his first goal for the Youth team in the 2024 [[Football NSW League]] Two season against [[South Coast Flame FC]], going on to finish that campaign with 7 goals in 26 games as the Jets Youth went unbeaten and earned promotion into FNSW League One<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-05 |title=Champion youth team shows Newcastle Jets on right flight path |url=https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/8719319/jets-youth-secure-nsw-npl1-spot-with-record-breaking-season/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.newcastleherald.com.au |language=en-au}}</ref>.

== Club career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===

==== Debut Season (2024-25) ====
Ahead of the [[2024–25 A-League Men|2024–25 A-League]] season, Dobson was awarded a two-year scholarship deal<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-08-16 |title=Will Dobson signs scholarship deal |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/will-dobson-signs-scholarship-deal/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref> by Head Coach [[Robert Stanton (soccer)|Robert Stanton]]. He made his debut off of the bench in round one against Melbourne City.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-20 |title=Academy Product Will Dobson makes Professional Debut |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/academy-product-will-dobson-makes-professional-debut/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref>. Dobson made his first start later on that season against Perth Glory.

'''Will Dobson''' (born 7 September 2007).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/dobson-will/IgtWVtI0/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en-AU}}</ref> is an Australian professional [[soccer]] player who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].

== Youth Career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===
Will Dobson joined the Newcastle Jets Academy in 2022 after a two year spell away with [[Weston Bears FC]], where he played in their U16s<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson - Player Statistics |url=https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?pID=207383317 |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=GameDay |language=en}}</ref> as a 14 year old.

He made his debut for the [[Newcastle Jets FC Youth|Jets Youth]] team in 2023, coming off the bench against [[Hurstville ZFC]] as a 15 year old<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match Centre - Dribl Match Centre |url=https://competitions.footballnsw.com.au/matchcentre/?m=3NPo2R5Z0m |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=competitions.footballnsw.com.au}}</ref>. He scored his first goal for the Youth team in the 2024 [[Football NSW League]] Two season against [[South Coast Flame FC]], going on to finish that campaign with 7 goals in 26 games as the Jets Youth went unbeaten and earned promotion into FNSW League One<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-05 |title=Champion youth team shows Newcastle Jets on right flight path |url=https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/8719319/jets-youth-secure-nsw-npl1-spot-with-record-breaking-season/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.newcastleherald.com.au |language=en-au}}</ref>.

He made his debut off of the bench in round one against Melbourne City.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-20 |title=Academy Product Will Dobson makes Professional Debut |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/academy-product-will-dobson-makes-professional-debut/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref>. Dobson made his first start later on that season against Perth Glory.

'''Will Dobson''' (born 7 September 2007).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson Stats {{!}} Soccerway |url=https://www.soccerway.com/player/dobson-will/IgtWVtI0/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.soccerway.com |language=en-AU}}</ref> is an Australian professional [[soccer]] player who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].

== Youth Career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===
Will Dobson joined the Newcastle Jets Academy in 2022 after a two year spell away with [[Weston Bears FC]], where he played in their U16s<ref>{{Cite web |title=Will Dobson - Player Statistics |url=https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?pID=207383317 |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=GameDay |language=en}}</ref> as a 14 year old.

He made his debut for the [[Newcastle Jets FC Youth|Jets Youth]] team in 2023, coming off the bench against [[Hurstville ZFC]] as a 15 year old<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match Centre - Dribl Match Centre |url=https://competitions.footballnsw.com.au/matchcentre/?m=3NPo2R5Z0m |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=competitions.footballnsw.com.au}}</ref>. He scored his first goal for the Youth team in the 2024 [[Football NSW League]] Two season against [[South Coast Flame FC]], going on to finish that campaign with 7 goals in 26 games as the Jets Youth went unbeaten and earned promotion into FNSW League One<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-05 |title=Champion youth team shows Newcastle Jets on right flight path |url=https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/8719319/jets-youth-secure-nsw-npl1-spot-with-record-breaking-season/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=www.newcastleherald.com.au |language=en-au}}</ref>.

== Club career ==

=== Newcastle Jets FC ===

==== Debut Season (2024-25) ====
Ahead of the [[2024–25 A-League Men|2024–25 A-League]] season, Dobson was awarded a two-year scholarship deal<ref>{{Cite web|date=2024-08-16 |title=Will Dobson signs scholarship deal |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/will-dobson-signs-scholarship-deal/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref> by Head Coach [[Robert Stanton (soccer)|Robert Stanton]]. He made his debut off of the bench in round one against Melbourne City.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-20 |title=Academy Product Will Dobson makes Professional Debut |url=https://newcastlejetsfc.com.au/news/academy-product-will-dobson-makes-professional-debut/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Newcastle Jets |language=en-AU}}</ref>. Dobson made his first start later on that season against Perth Glory.

Egon is the most serious and rigid member of the team. Of his hobbies, Egon states that he collects "[[spore]]s, [[Mold (fungus)|mold]]s, and [[fungus]]", and claims that, as a child, the only toy he ever had was "part of a [[Slinky]]", which he straightened out.
